parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the traction control system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle stalls or loses power
and the accelerator pedal may not respond.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air vent actuator can cause the air vents to malfunction, leading to discomfort and distraction while driving.
symptoms: The air vents make a clicking or knocking noise
the air vents do not respond to controls
and the air vents blow cold air in winter or hot air in summer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle stalls or loses power

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The doors lock and unlock independently

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents.
symptoms: the brakes feel spongy or soft
and the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Traction Control and ABS System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the traction control and ABS system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Warning lights for stabilizing system and ABS
traction control turns on and off

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of suspension and steering components can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
The failure of the brake system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
The failure of the electrical system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
The malfunction of the traction control system can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-misses.
symptoms: The traction control light comes on
and the stability control light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-misses.
symptoms: the transmission warning light comes on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduction of engine power can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-misses.
symptoms: the stability control light comes on
and the check engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or jerk, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-misses.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle moving without driver input can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls away without driver input
the gear shift indicator shows "Park" even though the vehicle is moving
and the vehicle crashes into other objects or vehicles.
